<subSubSection pageId="17" pageNumber="16" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="17.[836,1528,296,656]" pageId="17" pageNumber="16">
<emphasis box="[932,1205,297,325]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="16">Diagnostic Features.</emphasis>
This new lycosid spider closely resembles 
<taxonomicName authority="C.L.Koch, 1878" authorityName="C.L.Koch" authorityYear="1878" box="[1074,1528,333,362]" class="Arachnida" family="Lycosidae" genus="Pardosa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="17" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="astrigera">
<emphasis box="[1074,1310,333,362]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="16">Pardosa astrigera</emphasis>
C.L.Koch, 
<quantity box="[1464,1528,333,362]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.77012" pageId="17" pageNumber="16" unit="in" value="1878.0">1878</quantity>
</taxonomicName>
in the color pattern of carapace and 
<taxonomicName authority="Yin, Peng and Wang, 1996" authorityName="Yin, Peng and Wang" authorityYear="1996" class="Arachnida" family="Lycosidae" genus="Lycosa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="17" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="yunnanensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="16">Lycosa yunnanensis</emphasis>
Yin, Peng and Wang, 
<quantity box="[1296,1360,407,436]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.06984" pageId="17" pageNumber="16" unit="in" value="1996.0">1996</quantity>
</taxonomicName>
in the shape of the posterior margin of septum but differs from both taxa in (
<number box="[1011,1024,480,509]" pageId="17" pageNumber="16" value="1.0">1</number>
) leg formula and spination in tibia IV, (
<number box="[846,863,517,546]" pageId="17" pageNumber="16" value="2.0">2</number>
) leg II as long as III, (
<number box="[1192,1208,517,546]" pageId="17" pageNumber="16" value="3.0">3</number>
) epigynum ratio of a/b = 
<number box="[854,913,554,583]" pageId="17" pageNumber="16" value="0.71">0.71</number>
, (
<number box="[952,970,554,583]" pageId="17" pageNumber="16" value="4.0">4</number>
) strongly C-shaped guide pocket, (
<number box="[1501,1518,554,583]" pageId="17" pageNumber="16" value="5.0">5</number>
) distinctly cleft posterior epigynal margin, and (
<number box="[1447,1464,591,620]" pageId="17" pageNumber="16" value="6.0">6</number>
) eye measurements.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
